    {
      "id": "13b0a5796d6885eaba34db3d47aadb9098c9d615",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 110,
        "name": "Chris Gearing",
        "email": "chris.gearing@intel.com",
        "username": "chris",
        "inactive": true
      },
      "date": "2011-03-03 10:11:23.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 12:\n\nThe specification of 'suite'_ONLY is not supplied to the called suites like sanity, I can't vouch that this will not have knock on effects.\r\n\r\nAlso line 204 should also be deleted because it's superfluous.\r\n\r\nLastly can we add some comments to the group files provided to explain the purpose in some detail. The ability to insert #comments has been provided, but but then no comments inserted.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 12
    },
    {
      "id": "b2fb9453955e0c746a9c8f18131a3177aa2e5e3c",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 1,
        "name": "Robert Read",
        "email": "robert.read@intel.com",
        "username": "rread",
        "inactive": true
      },
      "date": "2011-03-03 22:22:14.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 12:\n\nI agree about adding comments to the group files, though the one's i've are just placeholders so there isn't much to say yet. I'm not sure what line you are referring to as being superfluous, I think our line numbers might be different. \n\nThe ${suite}_ONLY mechanism is not used inside the test suites. It was actually some old code that I added to acceptance-small.sh  while ago to add the ability to pass arguments to individual test suites.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 12
    },
